---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
import PageFooter from "../components/PageFooter.astro"

export const prerender = true
---

<BaseLayout title="Support | Packstack" description="Get help with Packstack — contact support and find answers to frequently asked questions.">
  <div class="bg-background min-h-screen">
    <header class="border-b border-border/50">
      <nav class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between px-4 md:px-8 py-3">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center">
          <img src="/packstack_logo_white.png" alt="Packstack" class="w-32" />
        </a>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 md:gap-6">
          <a href="/tools" class="text-softwhite hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm font-semibold no-underline">Tools</a>
          <a href="/learn" class="text-softwhite hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm font-semibold no-underline">Learn</a>
          <a href="https://app.packstack.io/auth/login" class="text-softwhite hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm font-semibold">Login</a>
          <a href="https://app.packstack.io/auth/register" class="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-dark text-white rounded-md py-1.5 px-4 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors no-underline">Sign Up</a>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-12 prose prose-invert prose-sm">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Support</h1>
      <p class="text-label text-sm mt-0 mb-10">We're here to help you get the most out of Packstack.</p>

      <p>
        If you need help, have a feature request, or want to report a bug, send us an email at
        <a href="mailto:jerad@packstack.io">jerad@packstack.io</a>. We typically respond within 24 hours.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-12">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>What is Packstack?</h3>
      <p>
        Packstack is a free gear tracking and packing list tool for backpackers and hikers.
        It helps you organize your inventory, build packing lists, and track your pack weight
        down to the ounce (or gram).
      </p>

      <h3>Is Packstack free?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Packstack is completely free to use. We may introduce optional premium features
        in the future, but the core gear tracking and packing list functionality will always
        be free.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I create an account?</h3>
      <p>
        You can sign up with your email address (we'll send you a one-time verification code),
        or sign in instantly with Google or Apple.
      </p>

      <h3>Can I import my gear from Lighterpack or a spreadsheet?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Packstack supports importing from Lighterpack CSV exports and generic CSV files.
        Go to your Inventory and look for the Import option.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I change my weight units?</h3>
      <p>
        Head to Settings in the app and you can switch between imperial (oz/lb) and metric (g/kg)
        units. All weights across the app will update automatically.
      </p>

      <h3>Can I share my packing list with others?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Each trip has a shareable link that anyone can view — no account required. You can
        find the share option on your trip's pack page.
      </p>

      <h3>What are Kits?</h3>
      <p>
        Kits are reusable groups of gear that you can quickly add to any packing list. For example,
        you might create a "Cook Kit" or "Sleep System" kit and add it to multiple trips without
        rebuilding the list each time.
      </p>

      <h3>Is my data backed up?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. All your data is stored securely on our servers and is backed up regularly. You can also
        export your inventory as a CSV at any time for your own records.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
      <p>
        Send us an email at <a href="mailto:jerad@packstack.io">jerad@packstack.io</a> and
        we'll process your account deletion within 30 days. All associated data will be permanently removed.
      </p>

      <h3>I found a bug. How do I report it?</h3>
      <p>
        Email us at <a href="mailto:jerad@packstack.io">jerad@packstack.io</a> with a description
        of the issue and any screenshots if possible. We appreciate the help!
      </p>
    </main>

    <PageFooter />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
